{
  "analysis": "We are at the `/app` directory with no prior commands executed. We need inspect the environment, confirm R/data availability, then create the Stan model and R analysis script, install RStan 2.32.7 if needed, run the sampling, and save posterior mean outputs.",
  "plan": "First I will list `/app`, inspect the dataset, check the R version, and see whether `rstan`/`StanHeaders` are already installed. This will determine whether installation is needed and what data dimensions/model variables we must pass to Stan.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -la /app\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "head -5 /app/data.csv; echo '---'; wc -l /app/data.csv\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "R --version\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "Rscript -e 'cat(\"rstan:\", as.character(requireNamespace(\"rstan\", quietly=TRUE)), \"\\n\"); cat(\"StanHeaders:\", as.character(requireNamespace(\"StanHeaders\", quietly=TRUE)), \"\\n\"); if (requireNamespace(\"rstan\", quietly=TRUE)) cat(packageVersion(\"rstan\"), \"\\n\")'\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    }
  ]
}

{
  "analysis": "The `/app` directory contains only `data.csv`. It has 68 data rows plus a header, with columns `y` and `n`. R 4.3.3 is installed, but neither `rstan` nor `StanHeaders` is installed, so we need to install RStan and Stan dependencies before running the analysis. Next I will inspect the data distribution and check/build system tools needed for compiling Stan models.",
  "plan": "I will print the dataset and summarize it in R to understand the empirical success rates. Then I will check OS information, compiler availability, CPU count, and whether required build tools/libraries are present. This informs the RStan installation approach and model parameterization.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat /app/data.csv\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "Rscript -e 'd <- read.csv(\"/app/data.csv\"); print(summary(d)); print(table(d$y)); cat(\"rows:\", nrow(d), \"\\n\"); cat(\"any 0<y<n:\", any(d$y>0 & d$y<d$n), \"\\n\")'\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat /etc/os-release 2>/dev/null | head -5; echo '---'; nproc; echo '---'; which gcc g++ make R Rscript || true; echo '---'; gcc --version 2>/dev/null | head -1; g++ --version 2>/dev/null | head -1\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "dpkg -l | grep -E 'build-essential|libcurl4-openssl-dev|libssl-dev|libxml2-dev|g\\+\\+' | head -20 || true\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ]
}

{
  "analysis": "The dataset has 68 rows with `y` successes and `n` trials, and many observed rates are low. R and build tools are present, but RStan/StanHeaders are not installed. We still need to install RStan 2.32.7 and dependencies, create the Stan model and R script, run sampling, and save posterior means.",
  "plan": "I will check whether Ubuntu provides suitable `r-cran-rstan`/`r-cran-stanheaders` packages, since that may be faster and more reliable than source installation. I will also check for key R package development libraries. Based on the package availability/version, I will choose an installation path.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "apt-cache policy r-cran-rstan r-cran-stanheaders 2>/dev/null || true\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "dpkg -l | grep -E 'libcurl4-openssl-dev|libssl-dev|libxml2-dev' || true\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "Rscript -e 'cat(\"curl:\", as.character(requireNamespace(\"curl\", quietly=TRUE)), \"\\n\"); cat(\"RCurl:\", as.character(requireNamespace(\"RCurl\", quietly=TRUE)), \"\\n\"); cat(\"xml2:\", as.character(requireNamespace(\"xml2\", quietly=TRUE)), \"\\n\")'\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    }
  ]
}

{
  "analysis": "The Ubuntu repositories only offer `r-cran-rstan`/`r-cran-stanheaders` version 2.32.5, but the task requires RStan 2.32.7. We need determine the best installation path. A practical route is to use apt to install binary dependencies for RStan, then install the exact CRAN/GitHub source versions of `StanHeaders` and `rstan` into the local R library so they shadow the apt versions if needed.",
  "plan": "I will inspect apt dependencies for `r-cran-rstan` and check CRAN availability/versions for `rstan` and `StanHeaders`. This will confirm whether source installation of 2.32.7 is possible from CRAN and what supporting packages/libraries are needed.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "apt-cache depends r-cran-rstan 2>/dev/null | head -80\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "apt-cache policy r-cran-remotes r-cran-rcpp r-cran-rcppeigen r-cran-rcppparallel r-cran-bh r-cran-inline r-cran-gridextra r-cran-v8 2>/dev/null || true\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "Rscript -e 'ap <- available.packages(repos=\"https://cloud.r-project.org\"); cat(\"rstan versions:\", paste(rownames(ap[ap[,\"Package\"]==\"rstan\",]), collapse=\", \"), \"\\n\"); cat(\"StanHeaders versions:\", paste(rownames(ap[ap[,\"Package\"]==\"StanHeaders\",]), collapse=\", \"), \"\\n\")'\n",
      "duration": 5.0
    }
  ]
}
